248"/**\n"\
249"\n"\
250" * @file Float.h\n"\
251" * @brief\n"\
252" * Here, float will be treated as bit vector with four attributes:\n"\
253" *\n"\
254"\n"\
255" * sign: \\n\t\n"\
256" * \t> Whether it has sign or not. \\n\n"\
257" *\n"\
258"\n"\
259" * exp:\t\\n\n"\
260" * \t> Exponent. It will be considered as unsigned integer, \\n\n"\
261" * \t> Which is the exponent of the [frac]\n"\
262" *\n"\
263"\n"\
264" * expbiasp: \\n\n"\
265" * \t> Exponent bias in order to be considered as zero. \\n\n"\
266" * \t> For handling possibly negative values of [exp] (such as 0.5) \\n\n"\
267" *\n"\
268"\n"\
269" * \t> Here, the value of exponent bias is limited with following rules:\n"\
270" * \t\t- It must be (2^([expbiasp]) - 1), and you are actually setting [expbiasp].\n"\
271" * \t\t- [expbiasp] must be between 1 and [exp].\n"\
272" *\n"\
273"\n"\
274" * frac: \\n\n"\
275" * \t> The actual \"value\" for floating point.\n"\
276" *\n"\
277"\n"\
278" * ==================\n"\
279" *\n"\
280"\n"\
281" * Following is the expected structure as bit vector: \\n\n"\
282" * [frac | exp | sign]\n"\
283" * \n"\
284" * Size of this will be calculated as: \\n\n"\
285" * [sign] + [exp] + [frac]\n"\
286" */\n"\

8603"\n"\
8604" * get_global_id(0) : oidx\t\\n\n"\
8605" * get_local_id(0) : iidx\t\\n\n"\
8606" *\n"\
8607"\n"\
8608" * Global: \\n\n"\
8609" * \tae2f_float_t[Out][In] : Weights\t\\n\n"\
8610" * \t, ae2f_float_t[Out] : Bias\t\\n\n"\
8611" *\t\t, ae2f_float_t[Inp]\t\t\\n\n"\
8612" *\t\t, ae2f_float_t[Out]\t\t\\n\n"\
8613" * \t, ae2f_float_t[Out] : Delta\t\\n\n"\
8614" * \t, ae2f_float_t[Out] : Goal\t\\n\n"\
8615" *\n"\
8616"\n"\
8617" * */\n"\
8618"__kernel void kFit(lr_t lr, __global ae2f_float_t* glob) {\n"\
8619"\tconst size_t\n"\
8620"\t\toidx = get_global_id(0)\n"\
8621"\t\t, osz = get_global_size(0)\n"\
8622"\t\t, iidx = get_global_id(1)\n"\
8623"\t\t, isz = get_global_size(1)\n"\
8624"\t\t;\n"\
8625"\n"\
8626"\tae2f_float_t\tdelta, v_tmp, v_tmp1;\n"\
8627"\n"\
8628"\tif(iidx == 0) {\n"\
8629"\t\t__ae2f_AnnSlpFetchDeltaOne_imp(\n"\
8630"\t\t\t\tv_tmp, v_tmp1\n"\
8631"\t\t\t\t, p_out /** out */\n"\
8632"\t\t\t\t, p_goal /** out_desired */ \n"\
8633"\t\t\t\t, ACT_DERIV\n"\
8634"\t\t\t\t, LOSS_DERIV\n"\
8635"\t\t\t\t, delta /** retdelta */\n"\
8636"\t\t\t\t, oidx\n"\
8637"\t\t\t\t, osz\n"\
8638"\t\t\t\t);\n"\
8639"\n"\
8640"\t\t/** delta */\n"\
8641"\t\tp_delta[oidx] = delta;\n"\
8642"\n"\
8643"\t\t__ae2f_AnnSlpFollowOneB_imp(\n"\
8644"\t\t\t\tp_bias[oidx]\t/** r_bias */\n"\
8645"\t\t\t\t, delta\t\t/** delta */\n"\
8646"\t\t\t\t, lr.m_bias\n"\
8647"\t\t\t\t);\n"\
8648"\t}\n"\
8649"\n"\
8650"\t__ae2f_AnnSlpFollowOneW_imp(\n"\
8651"\t\t\tp_inp[iidx] /** inp */\n"\
8652"\t\t\t, delta /** delta */\n"\
8653"\t\t\t, p_weight /** weight */\n"\
8654"\t\t\t, lr.m_weight\n"\
8655"\t\t\t, isz\n"\
8656"\t\t\t, iidx\n"\
8657"\t\t\t, osz\n"\
8658"\t\t\t, oidx\n"\
8659"\t\t\t);\n"\
8660"}\n"\
8661"\n"\
8662"/**\n"\
8663"\n"\
8664" * @brief\n"\
8665" * get_global_id(0):\toidx\n"\
8666" * get_local_id(0):\tiidx\n"\
8667" *\n"\
8668"\n"\
8669" * Global: \\n\n"\
8670" * \tae2f_float_t[Out][In] : Weights\t\\n\n"\
8671" * \t, ae2f_float_t[Out] : Bias\t\\n\n"\
8672" * \t, ae2f_float_t[Inp]\t\t\\n\n"\
8673" * \t, ae2f_float_t[Out] : Delta\t\\n\n"\
8674" * */\n"\
8675"__kernel void kFollow(lr_t lr, __global ae2f_float_t* glob) {\n"\
8676"\tconst size_t\n"\
8677"\t\toidx = get_global_id(0)\n"\
8678"\t\t, osz = get_global_size(0)\n"\
8679"\t\t, iidx = get_global_id(1)\n"\
8680"\t\t, isz = get_global_size(1)\n"\
8681"\t\t;\n"\
8682"\n"\
8683"\t__ae2f_AnnSlpFollowOneW_imp(\n"\
8684"\t\t\tp_inp[iidx] /** inp */\n"\
8685"\t\t\t, p_delta[oidx] /** delta */\n"\
8686"\t\t\t, p_weight /** weight */\n"\
8687"\t\t\t, lr.m_weight\n"\
8688"\t\t\t, isz\n"\
8689"\t\t\t, iidx\n"\
8690"\t\t\t, osz\n"\
8691"\t\t\t, oidx\n"\
8692"\t\t\t);\n"\
8693"\n"\
8694"\tif(iidx == 0) {\n"\
8695"\t\t__ae2f_AnnSlpFollowOneB_imp(\n"\
8696"\t\t\t\tp_bias[oidx] /** r_bias */\n"\
8697"\t\t\t\t, p_delta[oidx] /** delta */\n"\
8698"\t\t\t\t, lr.m_bias\n"\
8699"\t\t\t\t);\n"\
8700"\t}\n"\

8713#define __ae2fVK_AnnSlpMkFndMemProp_imp(

8716

8723)\

8731 (r_memtypeidx)--

8733 & vkpropflag_req)

8735 );

9042/**
9043
9044 * @brief
9045 * Make slp with OpenCL compute shader.
9046 *
9047
9048 * @details
9049 * The shader itself is incomplete. \n
9050 * For using it you will need to define three macros as function. \n
9051 * Below is the required snippet.
9052 *
9053
9054 * #define ACT(const ae2f_float_t) -> ae2f_float_t \n
9055 * #define ACT_DERIV(const ae2f_float_t) -> ae2f_float_t \n
9056 * #define LOSS_DERIV(
9057 * ae2f_float_t* retval
9058 * const ae2f_float_t* const out
9059 * , const ae2f_float_t* const out_desired
9060 * , const size_t index
9061 * , const size_t length_out_goal
9062 * );
9063 *
9064
9065 * @param vkcldeclaration
9066 * @param vkcldefinition
9067 * */
9068#define __ae2fVK_AnnSlpMk_imp(
9069 /** tparam */
9070
9071
9072 /** param */
9073 /* , ae2fVK_AnnSlpMk_t */ v_mk,
9074 /* ae2f_float_t* const */ weight_opt,
9075 /* ae2f_float_t* const */ bias_opt,
9076 /* ae2f_float_t* const */ cache_opt,
9077 /* const uint32_t */ inc,
9078 /* const uint32_t */ outc,
9079 /* ae2f_opt const size_t */ prm_offset,
9080 /* ae2f_opt const size_t */ extra,
9081 /* ae2f_optae2f_AnnAct_t* const */ act,
9082 /* ae2f_optae2f_AnnAct_t* const */ actderiv,
9083 /* ae2f_AnnLoss_t* const */ lossderiv,
9084 /* ae2f_float_t */ learningrate,
9085 /* ae2f_float_t */ learningrate_bias,
9086 /* const VkDevice */ vkdev,
9087 /* const VkPhysicalDeviceMemoryProperties */ vkmemprops,
9088 /* ae2f_optVkAllocationCallbacks* const */ vkalloccalls,
9089 /* ae2f_opt constchar* const */ vkcldeclaration,
9090 /* ae2f_opt constchar* const */ vkcldefinition \
9091)\
9092{
9093 assert((vkdev) && "Vulkan device null check");
9094 assert((lossderiv) && "lossderiv must be specified.");
9095
9096 (v_mk).m_reterr = ae2f_errGlob_OK;
9097 (v_mk).m_clout.m_void = NULL;
9098
9099 do {
9100 __ae2f_AnnSlpMk_imp(
9101 (v_mk).m_union.m_base, (weight_opt)
9102 , (bias_opt), (cache_opt)
9103 , (inc), (outc)
9104 , ((prm_offset) + sizeof(ae2fVK_AnnSlp) - sizeof(ae2f_AnnSlp))
9105 , (extra)
9106 , (act), (actderiv), (lossderiv)
9107 , (learningrate), (learningrate_bias)
9108 );
9109
9110 if((v_mk).m_union.m_base.m_ptr->m_Slp[0].m_inc > UINT32_MAX) {
9111 assert(!"Input size is too large");
9112 (v_mk).m_reterr |= ae2f_errGlob_WRONG_OPERATION;
9113 break;
9114 }
9115
9116 if((v_mk).m_union.m_base.m_ptr->m_Slp[0].m_outc > UINT32_MAX) {
9117 assert(!"Output size is too large");
9118 (v_mk).m_reterr |= ae2f_errGlob_WRONG_OPERATION;
9119 break;
9120 }
9121
9122 __ae2f_AnnSlpInitInpSz_imp((v_mk).m_union.m_base.m_alloccount, 0, 0, 0, inc, outc);
9123
9124 (v_mk).m_union.m_base.m_alloccount =
9125 (v_mk).m_union.m_base.m_alloccount
9126 - sizeof(ae2f_AnnSlp)
9127 + ae2f_CmpGetGt(
9128 (sizeof(ae2f_float_t) * (outc) * 2)
9129 , (sizeof(ae2f_float_t) * ((outc) + (inc)))
9130 )
9131 ; /** weight, bias, deltacache */
9132
9133 (v_mk).m_union.m_alter.m_ptr->m_vkdev = vkdev;
9134 (v_mk).m_union.m_alter.m_ptr->m_vkalloccalls = vkalloccalls;
9135
9136 /** Allocate the global memory */
9137 __ae2fVK_AnnSlpMkAllocVKMem_imp(
9138 break;
9139 , (v_mk).m_union.m_base.m_alloccount
9140 , (v_mk).m_union.m_alter.m_ptr->m_vkres
9141 , (v_mk).m_union.m_alter.m_ptr->m_vkglobbuf
9142 , (v_mk).m_union.m_alter.m_ptr->m_vkglobdevmem
9143 , (v_mk).m_reterr
9144 , (v_mk).m_vkinfo.m_buf
9145 , (v_mk).m_vkinfo.m_alloc
9146 , VK_BUFFER_USAGE_STORAGE_BUFFER_BIT
9147 , VK_SHARING_MODE_EXCLUSIVE
9148 , (vkdev)
9149 , (v_mk).m_vkstack.m_memreq
9150 , (vkalloccalls)
9151 , (v_mk).m_union.m_alter.m_i /* v_memtypeidx */
9152 , UCHAR_MAX
9153 , VK_MEMORY_PROPERTY_HOST_VISIBLE_BIT
9154 , vkmemprops
9155 );
9156
9157 /** the local memory */
9158 __ae2fVK_AnnSlpMkAllocVKMem_imp(
9159 break;
